channel.title: Help with boolean errors
channel.description:
title says it all.I got 9 errors in my compiler
client.java:9029: in is already defined in client private java.io.InputStream in; ^ client.java:9049: incompatible types found : java.io.InputStream required: boolean in = s.getInputStream(); ^ client.java:9075: incomparable types: boolean and <nulltype> if(in != null) in.close(); ^ client.java:9075: boolean cannot be dereferenced if(in != null) in.close(); ^ client.java:9079: incompatible types found : <nulltype> required: boolean in = null; ^ client.java:9210: boolean cannot be dereferenced in.read(inStream.buffer, 0, forceRead); ^ client.java:13786: boolean cannot be dereferenced int avail = in.available(); ^ client.java:13789: boolean cannot be dereferenced packetType = in.read() & 0xff; ^ client.java:13796: boolean cannot be dereferenced packetSize = in.read() & 0xff; ^ client.java:14029: cannot find symbol symbol : method SummonNewNPC(int) location: class client SummonNewNPC(2880); ^ client.java:14034: cannot find symbol symbol : method SummonNewNPC(int) location: class client SummonNewNPC(49); ^ client.java:14039: cannot find symbol symbol : method SummonNewNPC(int) location: class client SummonNewNPC(795); ^ client.java:14044: cannot find symbol symbol : method SummonNewNPC(int) location: class client SummonNewNPC(509); ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API.
